subSubSection.paragraph:
Coloration.
Recently fixed small specimen (
Fig. 6
): eyes dark brown; dorsal surface of head mottled dark brown, dorsal parts of pereonites 4 and 7 dark brown; other body parts yellowish white with indistinct brown speckles; antennae white and partly pale brown; gnathopods and pereopods white. Preserved large specimens (
Fig. 7
): eyes dark brown; dorsal surface of head mottled dark brown, pereonites 4 and 7 dark brown, other pereonites, pleonites and urosomites in male brown, pereonites 3, 5 and 6, pleonites and urosomites in female pale brown; antenna 2 peduncle white and partly dark brown; other appendages white.
